    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Welcome to Jekyll!]]></title>
    <link href="/blog/jekyll/update/2014/01/04/welcome-to-jekyll"/>
    <updated>2014-01-04T03:42:44Z</updated>
    <id>/blog/jekyll/update/2014/01/04/welcome-to-jekyll</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>You&#39;ll find this post in your <code>_posts</code> directory - edit this post and re-build (or run with the <code>-w</code> switch) to see your changes!
To add new posts, simply add a file in the <code>_posts</code> directory that follows the convention: YYYY-MM-DD-name-of-post.ext.</p>

<p>Jekyll also offers powerful support for code snippets:</p>

<p><div class="highlight"><pre><code class="ruby"><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">print</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">em</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="n">hi</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">name</span><span class="p">)</span>
  <span class="nb">puts</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">quot</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="no">Hi</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="c1">#{name}&amp;quot;</span>
<span class="k">end</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="sr">/em&gt;hi(&amp;#39;Tom&amp;#39;)&lt;/</span><span class="nb">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>

<span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">h1</span><span class="o">&gt;=&amp;</span><span class="n">gt</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="n">prints</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="c1">#39;Hi, Tom&amp;#39; to STDOUT.&lt;/h1&gt;</span>

<span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="nb">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></p>

<p>Check out the <a href="http://jekyllrb.com">Jekyll docs</a> for more info on how to get the most out of Jekyll. File all bugs/feature requests at <a href="https://github.com/mojombo/jekyll">Jekyll&#39;s GitHub repo</a>.</p>
]]></content>
